description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Matrons Admin Assistant on the Emergency Management Unit. We are looking for experienced candidates with an excellent level of administration, interpersonal and organisational skills. The role will be key in supporting the EMU Matron with a variety of administrative duties. Confidentiality is key to this role and a high level of professionalism is expected. You will have excellent IT skills including experience in MS systems including Outlook, Word, Excel and Teams. Experience in roster planning would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is 37.5 hours per week and can be worked over 4 or 5 days mon-fri. Hours of work can be negotiated. A start time of 0730 would be required for 3 of those days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact stacy.clark3@nhs.net if you require further information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameStacy ClarkJob titleMatronEmail addressstacy.clark3@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
